<br>
Tethtoril <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uhungri.showPublicProfile?language=EN>hungri</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/19/02 7:06:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1273.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   halfling vs ogre</span><hr size=1> i played a halfing to 55 n a bit. was disatisfied when playing next to large race warriors, so i bit bullet and started over, i now play a 54 ogre war. the ogre is by far a better base race then the halfling was for me. as far as being IN THE DAMN WAY all the time, halflings have there own problem with being short and needing a boost up large stairs and such, its a trade off in that respective. the halfing is in full hate and has some decent no drop weapons and items, that are better then what ive managed for the ogre so far, he still out damages and out tanks the halfing, im glad i did it. it was definintaly worth remaking the warrior. i break out the halfling every so often for fear cr and so on and i miss the hps and dam output of the ogre imeadiatly. just my 2coppers <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/usarmaldor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sarmaldor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 83<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/19/02 8:10:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1273.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: halfling vs ogre</span><hr size=1> Well, Im an Ogre and I love it. I dont preach the Gospel of front stun immunity because I dont think I've ever seen it cause a change in aggro - avoids an annoying effect and I like it. Getting stuck sucks, but carry potions on you for outdoor zones and get  cobalt bracer for indoor and your alright. It's cool being big and cool bsing with your guildmates about smashing them, eating all the cake, you sure wish there were more Ogre women instead of ugly half-elves, etc. The starting stamina is real nice and you can max more easily for exp groups when you cant get riotous health but over all everyone is going to be similar in raid.<br>
<br>
Ogre however, are not the most popular choice of warrior and you wont see too many. Seems Barbarian by far is the choice of warriors - half-elves in second. If you want to look like everyone else - go for it. <br>
<br>
That being said, I think the most uber warrior on my server is a half-elf: he is a good warrior that can grab aggo when needed, keep aggro off when he isnt the main tank, pays attention to the raid and the guild chat, etc. So race really doesnt matter if you are just trying to be a damn good warrior.<br>
<br>
However, if you want to have a little fun with your guildmates constantly joking you (and you back with them), want to LOOK like a big ol' meat shield, want a little uniqueness (dont say gnome warrior either - plenty of &quot;original&quot; warriors out there - a rare is a female troll warrior), and want to enjoy some pretty nice racial features - no stun and good starting stats - then do an orge.<br>
<br>
